subject: Olympic Games (2014)
Skiing
World Cup (Skiing)
lead_paragraph: Jessica Lindell-Vikarby of Sweden won the race with an aggregate time of 2 minutes 17.92 seconds, edging Mikaela Shiffrin of the United States by 0.09 of a second, or about two feet.
